  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: devel v2022.02.01\r\nOS & Version: Linux debian\r\nCommit hash : 2cc49f454ffecd9e17d5b04c1cd68b393cd0bbe7\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nRPC daemon runs normally when erigon runs with --txpool.disable argument. This was the case before the extrnal txpool update. I don't need the txpool and would like to keep it disabled.\r\n`erigon --txpool.disable --datadir /erigon --maxpeers 25 --ethash.dagdir /erigon/erigon-ethash --port 30305 --private.api.addr=localhost:9090`\r\n`rpcdaemon --datadir /erigon --private.api.addr=localhost:9090 --http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace --txpool.api.addr=localhost:9090 --http.addr 192.168.1.2 --http.port 8650 --ws`\r\nSame thing happens without the `--txpool.api.addr=localhost:9090` argument on rpcdaemon\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nRPC daemon crashes\r\n```\r\nDB schemas compatible                    reader=5.0.0 database=5.0.0\r\nrpc filters: subscribing to Erigon events\r\nHTTP endpoint opened                     url=192.168.1.2:8650 ws=true ws.compression=false grpc=false\r\nrpc filters: error subscribing to pending transactions err=\"rpc error: code = Unimplemented desc = unknown service txpool.Txpool\"\r\ninterfaces compatible                    remote_db= client=5.1.0 server=5.1.0\r\ninterfaces compatible                    remote_service=eth_backend client=3.0.0 server=3.0.0\r\ninterfaces compatible                    remote_service=mining client=1.0.0 server=1.0.0\r\nensure version                           remote_service=tx_pool error=\"rpc error: code = Unimplemented desc = unknown service txpool.Txpool\"\r\nExiting...\r\nRPC server shutting down\r\n```\r\n",
