    "body": "@geomad - it's happening because: \r\n-  `localhost:9090` - has real GRPC server (Erigon's private API)\r\n- `--txpool.disable` - this flag means \"don't start any TxPool-related functionality inside Erigon, I will run TxPool as individual process\". So, Erigon doesn't serve txpool api's on `localhost:9090` in this case. \r\n-  But in RPCDaemon you set `--txpool.api.addr=localhost:9090` - RPCDaemon connecting to Erigon, asking \"do you have TxPool API?\" and Erigon says \"Nope\" (`unknown service txpool.Txpool`)\r\n- What you need to do: change `--txpool.api.addr=localhost:9090` to another port (by agreement it's 9094). RPCDaemon then will try to connect there (in background, non-blocking) until success. \r\n- You can start or not start (up to you) external TxPool on `9094` port https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/tree/devel/cmd/txpool#external-mode\r\n\r\n\r\nI'm happy to make it more user-friendly - but don't know how yet - feel free to advise\r\n",
